result.execSummary:
The defendant Rhonda M Allen-Miller was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Rhonda M Allen-Miller in court.  Attorney Travis Schwantes in court for Rhonda M Allen-Miller.  Attorney Elaine B. Fehrs in court for State of Wisconsin. Deputy Court Clerk: SD. 
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. 

AS TO COUNT 1: Defendant ordered to serve 5 MONTHS in the House of Correction.  Court will allow Huber release.

AS TO COUNT 2:  Defendant ordered to serve 2 days in the House of Correction, with 2 days time served.  THIS IS A TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.  

AS TO COUNT 1: Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation for 18 months with the following conditions:

- Report for probation by 5pm on 10/21/2022.
- Complete a batters intervention program.
- Mental health assessment, comply with recommended treatment.
- Alcohol and drug assessment and comply with any treatment deemed necessary by the department.
- Maintain absolute sobriety.
- No use of possession of firearms.
- Full time work.
- No contact with victim.
- Provide a DNA sample by 5pm on 10/21/2022.
- Pay the Domestic Abuse Assessment fee.
- Court set restitution at $300.00 made payable to SA.

- Court WAIVES all non-mandatory costs, fees and surcharges.  Defendant to pay mandatory costs and surcharges (including DNA and DV) during period of probation.  If unpaid a civil judgment will be ordered filed against the defendant.

Court will allow any probation treatment and assessments to be completed at the VA facilities.  

Defendant advised of appeal rights.

Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank.
